# Join the Band Dance Party!

Coldplay and Code.org believe in the “Higher Power” of computer science education for every student, in every classroom around the world. That’s why we’re teaming up to get students everywhere to code and dance — let’s celebrate the magic of computer science and music! 

Join the party by using Code.org’s Dance Party activity to code your own choreography to Coldplay’s “Higher Power.” Get creative with classic moves, and have fun with a few new visuals and dancer formations!

Post or submit your creations for Coldplay and Code.org to see, and we’ll share the best ones on social media. Plus, you’ll get a chance to win tickets to see Coldplay on tour, or a chance for your classroom to video chat with the band.

We can’t wait to see and share what you create! 



## How to create your entry
<ol>
<li>Start <a href="https://code.org/dance">Dance Party</a></li>
<li>Learn to code your own dance in a short 10-step tutorial</li>
<li>On the final level, code an awesome dance to Coldplay’s song, “Higher Power.” (Don’t forget to try out the special “Higher Power” background effect!)</li>
<li>Click “Finish” to get a share link to your project.</li>
<li>For extra fun, make a video of yourself dancing along with your code!</li>
</ol>

